Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.48,0:40:58.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,或其他人\N{\rENG}or about someone else that might
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.20,0:41:00.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,有没有受伤 这样\N{\rENG}have accidentally been killed, and stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.33,0:41:04.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是有句话吗 叫老二的事最重要\N{\rENG}Does not say it all? Penis first and the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.31,0:41:08.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,老二 老二\N{\rENG}Penis! Penis!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.19,0:41:11.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们能从纯粹的性别角度解释\N{\rENG}But if you can explain it on strictly gender terms
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.18,0:41:14.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们为什么 或者说为什么女人要浪费时间\N{\rENG}why do you, or why does any woman waste time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.41,0:41:16.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,不厌其烦的尝试改变一个男人呢\N{\rENG}getting mad at or bother to trying to change a man?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.75,0:41:19.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 这是生物学 到底是什么问题呢\N{\rENG}Exactly! It's all biology. What is the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.37,0:41:22.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,你太会转移话题了\N{\rENG}And you are so, so good at turnings things around ...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.16,0:41:24.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不 我只是想说  - 他是个天才\N{\rENG}- NO... I'm just trying to say that.  - He is a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.30,0:41:26.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就叫鸡蛋里面挑骨头\N{\rENG}it's like getting pissed at frog for being green.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.72,0:41:29.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没错  - 听了这么久\N{\rENG}- Yes! Exactly!  - Hearing all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.45,0:41:31.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就想 天长地久相爱\N{\rENG}I wonder if this idea of a love
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.55,0:41:34.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,这种事还和我们有关吗\N{\rENG}affair that lasts forever is still relevant to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.75,0:41:36.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,都知道\N{\rENG}I mean we know that we are
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.33,0:41:38.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们最终会分开\N{\rENG}going to break up eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.49,0:41:39.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,毫无疑问\N{\rENG}Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.45,0:41:42.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你的父母还在一起吗  - 没有\N{\rENG}- Are your parents are still together?  - No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.07,0:41:43.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有 那你的呢\N{\rENG}No and what about yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.32,0:41:45.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,在一起 但他们可以离婚\N{\rENG}They are, but they could divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.92,0:41:48.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们有钱的话\N{\rENG}I think if they had more money,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.33,0:41:49.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,估计早就离了\N{\rENG}they would not still be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.84,0:41:51.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,老天 你们都太实际了\N{\rENG}God, you guys are so practical,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.86,0:41:54.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真是生错了年代\N{\rENG}I was born into the wrong generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.48,0:41:56.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,我曾祖母\N{\rENG}My grandmother's mother
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.46,0:41:58.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,在她临终前\N{\rENG}wrote to our whole family
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.08,0:42:01.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,留下了二十六页的长信\N{\rENG}a 26-page letter from her deathbed
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.15,0:42:02.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,她花了三页去说\N{\rENG}and she spent three pages
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.84,0:42:05.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,她为一部戏设计的服装\N{\rENG}on the costume she did for a play...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.00,0:42:06.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,而仅用一段来说她的丈夫\N{\rENG}and only one paragraph on her husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.78,0:42:07.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,她也是演员吗\N{\rENG}Was she an actress too?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.90,0:42:09.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 她是个\N{\rENG}No... she was...a...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.38,0:42:12.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,英语“女裁缝”怎么说\N{\rENG}Comment on dit " couturière "?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.50,0:42:14.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,女裁缝\N{\rENG}Seamstress.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.63,0:42:16.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,她有很多\N{\rENG}And she had all these
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.46,0:42:20.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,不错的朋友 而关于我曾祖父\N{\rENG}wonderful friends and about my great-grandfather
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.29,0:42:22.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,她仅提到三件事\N{\rENG}She mentioned three events:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.11,0:42:24.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,他去参战 因为他的工作搬家\N{\rENG}He went to war, we moved because of his job
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.83,0:42:26.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,他死了\N{\rENG}And he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.77,0:42:29.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,她的忠告是\N{\rENG}Her big advice was
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.24,0:42:31.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要在浪漫的爱情上消耗太多\N{\rENG}not to be too consumed with romantic love
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.03,0:42:34.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,友谊和工作\N{\rENG}Friendships and work, she said,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.11,0:42:36.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,才给我带来真正的快乐\N{\rENG}brought to her the most happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.31,0:42:37.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,我再同意不过了\N{\rENG}I could not agree more,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.80,0:42:40.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们就是被这样教育长大的 对吧\N{\rENG}I mean that's the thing that fucks us up right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.38,0:42:42.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,只有这种精神伴侣\N{\rENG}This idea of a soul mate of someone
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.88,0:42:44.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,才能让我们变得完整\N{\rENG}who would come to complete us
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.72,0:42:47.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,帮助我们承担生活中的问题\N{\rENG}and save us from having to take care of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.99,0:42:51.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,对于斯特凡诺斯 我将标准降得非常低\N{\rENG}With Stefanos, I set the bar extremely low
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.02,0:42:54.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道他做不到我的要求\N{\rENG}I know he is not gonna meet any of my needs
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.31,0:42:55.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,太难了\N{\rENG}Definitely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.36,0:42:58.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,那你的祖母呢 她是你的精神伴侣吗\N{\rENG}So what about Grandma? Was she your soul mate?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.59,0:43:00.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,说得好听 不过\N{\rENG}Sounds appealing but actually
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.22,0:43:02.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,你祖母其实更加理性一些\N{\rENG}your grandmother was more rational than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.59,0:43:05.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,她很独立 也这样要求我\N{\rENG}She took cared of herself and asked me to do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.85,0:43:07.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我们有足够的空间 协商一致\N{\rENG}With plenty of room to meet in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.76,0:43:09.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,听起来很理想\N{\rENG}Yeah, that sounds ideal
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.27,0:43:10.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,那确实很理想\N{\rENG}That's is, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.04,0:43:13.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,很显然 我妻子今天不在这\N{\rENG}But it must be obvious that my wife is not here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.79,0:43:15.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们从来不是一个人\N{\rENG}We were never one person,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.41,0:43:18.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,是两个独立的人 我们也很喜欢这样\N{\rENG}always two, we preferred it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.14,0:43:19.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,真是美丽的故事\N{\rENG}That is so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.46,0:43:21.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,我认为我的丈夫\N{\rENG}I think my husband is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.37,0:43:25.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,总是想吞并我\N{\rENG}always trying to almost colonize me, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.06,0:43:26.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我吞并你吗\N{\rENG}I colonize you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.87,0:43:30.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 但我也在吞并你 亲爱的\N{\rENG}Yes but I colonize you, too, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.73,0:43:32.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Well ... Ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.24,0:43:34.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,但在最后的时日\N{\rENG}But at the end of the day
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.23,0:43:36.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你会发现\N{\rENG}It's not the love of one
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.00,0:43:38.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不是爱着一个人 而是爱着这种生活\N{\rENG}other person that matters it's the love of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.85,0:43:39.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,那太好了 帕特里克\N{\rENG}That's good to know, Patrick,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.91,0:43:41.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为生活我能自己掌控\N{\rENG}because life I can handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.79,0:43:43.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,而阿里阿德涅\N{\rENG}Ariadni, on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.67,0:43:45.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们都知道希腊出悲剧 对吧\N{\rENG}We all know that the Greeks invented tragedy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.83,0:43:46.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,而且她还来自玛尼\N{\rENG}and on top of that it stems
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.88,0:43:51.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,狂躁这个词就来源于此地\N{\rENG}from the original Mani, which is short for Mania.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.01,0:43:59.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,对了 如果今晚我们去不了旅馆\N{\rENG}Hey, guys if we can not make that hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.10,0:44:01.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们能退掉它或你们自己去住吗\N{\rENG}room tonight could you get a refund or use it yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.95,0:44:03.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 我们退不了款\N{\rENG}No... we do not get a refund.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.53,0:44:05.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们不想住吗\N{\rENG}Are you trying to get out of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.92,0:44:07.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是 这份礼物太棒了\N{\rENG}No, it's such a great gift you've given us.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.50,0:44:09.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,但还要打行李\N{\rENG}But I'm so stressed getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.15,0:44:11.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有女孩们 压力太大\N{\rENG}all the packing ready, with the girls...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.42,0:44:12.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不 不  - 这样吧\N{\rENG}- No, no...  - We made a deal guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.32,0:44:14.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们帮你看孩子 你们好好享受\N{\rENG}We will watch the kids, you're gonna love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.59,0:44:18.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 慢慢走去旅馆  - 会非常棒的\N{\rENG}- It's a fantastic walk to  - It's really really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.39,0:44:20.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那感觉非常美妙 你们不会后悔的  - 没错\N{\rENG}- the hotel You won't regret it.  - It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.67,0:44:23.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,不去的话 我们可是会生气的\N{\rENG}And we would be very offended if you don't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.27,0:44:24.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Ok...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.29,0:44:25.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢你们\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.31,0:44:30.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,当我想起我的丈夫\N{\rENG}Well... when I think of my husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.31,0:44:32.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,我非常想念\N{\rENG}what I miss the most about him
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.22,0:44:36.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,夜晚他躺在我身边的感觉\N{\rENG}is the way he used to lie down next to me at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.79,0:44:40.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,有时他会把胳膊横在我的胸前\N{\rENG}Sometimes his arm would stretch along my chest,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.86,0:44:45.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,我动不了 甚至要憋住呼吸\N{\rENG}and I could not move, I... I even held my breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.43,0:44:49.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我感到 安心\N{\rENG}But I felt safe
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.35,0:44:50.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,完整\N{\rENG}Complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.97,0:44:53.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也想念\N{\rENG}And... I miss the way
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.57,0:44:56.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,他走在街上吹着口哨的样子\N{\rENG}he was whistling walking down the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.91,0:45:00.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,每次做什么我都会想他怎么做\N{\rENG}And every time I do something I think of what he would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.50,0:45:03.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,天冷了 要披上围巾\N{\rENG}when it's cold today, wear a scarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.20,0:45:10.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是之后 我渐渐忘却细节\N{\rENG}But lately I've been forgetting little things.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.41,0:45:15.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,记忆在不断褪色 我开始忘记他\N{\rENG}It's sort of fading and I'm starting to forget him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.32,0:45:16.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就像\N{\rENG}And it's like ...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.88,0:45:20.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,我又失去了他\N{\rENG}like losing him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.68,0:45:24.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以有时 我努力回想\N{\rENG}So sometimes I make myself remember
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.34,0:45:26.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,他脸庞的每一处\N{\rENG}every detail of his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.85,0:45:31.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,眼睛的颜色 唇齿的样子\N{\rENG}The exact color of his eyes, his lips, his teeth,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.01,0:45:34.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,他的皮肤和头发的触感\N{\rENG}the texture of his skin, his hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.23,0:45:38.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,这一切记忆都随着时间流走了\N{\rENG}That was all gone by the time he went.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.16,0:45:42.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,但有时 偶尔 只是偶尔\N{\rENG}And sometimes... not always, but sometimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.73,0:45:44.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,我能非常清楚的看到他\N{\rENG}I can actually see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.08,0:45:47.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,就好像拨开云雾 他就在那里\N{\rENG}It's as if a cloud moves away and there he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.75,0:45:49.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,我几乎能碰到他\N{\rENG}And I could almost touch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.72,0:45:53.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,突然 真实回到了眼前\N{\rENG}But then... the real world rushes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.86,0:45:56.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,他再次消失了\N{\rENG}And he vanishes again.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.89,0:45:59.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,曾几何时 每天早晨\N{\rENG}For a while, I did this every morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.35,0:46:02.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,天刚亮的时候 我都会看到他\N{\rENG}when the sun was not too bright outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.04,0:46:05.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,可不知为何 他又会消失在阳光下\N{\rENG}But the sun somehow makes him vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.42,0:46:09.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,他出现又消失\N{\rENG}And he appears and he disappears,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.88,0:46:13.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,像日出和日落\N{\rENG}like a sunrise and a sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.00,0:46:16.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,一切都那么短暂\N{\rENG}Anything, so ephemeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.91,0:46:20.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,正如我们的生活\N{\rENG}It's just like our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.47,0:46:24.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们出现又消失\N{\rENG}We appear and we disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.24,0:46:27.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们对有些人来说很重要\N{\rENG}And we are so important to some,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.83,0:46:31.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,可我们又只是擦肩而过\N{\rENG}but we are just... passing through.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.52,0:46:36.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,敬 擦肩而过\N{\rENG}To "passing through"
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.90,0:46:41.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,敬 擦肩而过\N{\rENG}To "Passing through"
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.11,0:46:53.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,终于 他在窗户的倒映下看清了自己的脸\N{\rENG}And eventually he catches his face in the window's reflection
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.75,0:46:56.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,他意识到自己已不再是那个9岁的小男孩了\N{\rENG}And he realizes he's no longer a 9 year old boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.06,0:46:57.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,对吧 他突然之间变老了 有了胡子\N{\rENG}Right? He's suddenly old, he's got a beard
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.99,0:47:00.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 眼睛里水雾缭绕  - 确实让人难过\N{\rENG}- and his eyes are watery  - This one seems sad
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.98,0:47:02.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,开始我还以为你要给我讲故事\N{\rENG}At first I thought you were going to tell me a story
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.69,0:47:04.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是关于一个人臆想出一个朋友的那个\N{\rENG}about a guy that has an imaginary friend
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.55,0:47:05.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,哪个\N{\rENG}Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.21,0:47:08.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,他五十多岁的时候 那个虚拟朋友又出现了\N{\rENG}When in his 50s, the imaginary  friend shows up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.53,0:47:09.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,和一只蜂鸟一起\N{\rENG}With the hummingbird?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.59,0:47:11.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没错 就是这个  - 你喜欢吗\N{\rENG}- Yes, that!  - You liked that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.45,0:47:12.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,很有趣\N{\rENG}It's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.74,0:47:14.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,还记得你让我看过的那封信吗\N{\rENG}Remember that letter
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.37,0:47:16.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,你二十岁时写给\N{\rENG}that you let me read that you wrote
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.52,0:47:18.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,四十岁的自己的那封信\N{\rENG}when you were 20 to yourself at 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.61,0:47:19.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然 我还记得第一句话\N{\rENG}Yes, I remember the first sentence:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.78,0:47:22.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,亲爱的四十岁的杰西 但愿你没有离婚\N{\rENG}Dear 40-year-old Jesse, I hope you're not divorced
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.38,0:47:23.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不记得有这部分了\N{\rENG}No I did not even remember that part,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.91,0:47:26.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是想说那封信里还提到别的事情\N{\rENG}I meant to all the other things in that letter
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.25,0:47:29.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,你还是那个你 我们总觉得自己会成长\N{\rENG}You're the same guy, I mean, we always think that we are evolving
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.69,0:47:31.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,可我们并无力改变多少\N{\rENG}But we can not change that much
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.74,0:47:33.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你知道我是怎样看待我的变化的  - 怎样\N{\rENG}- You know how I think I've changed the most.  - How?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.85,0:47:36.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我年轻的时候总希望时间可以过得快一点\N{\rENG}When I was younger I just wanted time to speed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.65,0:47:37.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,为什么\N{\rENG}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.50,0:47:40.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为那样 我就可以做我自己\N{\rENG}So I can be on my own, so I can be free from my parents
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.34,0:47:41.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,摆脱掉家长和学校的一切束缚\N{\rENG}and school and all that shit, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.57,0:47:44.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我希望自己闭上眼 一睁眼就变成了成年人\N{\rENG}I just wanted to close my eyes and wake up and be an adult
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.91,0:47:46.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在一切都如我所愿成为现实\N{\rENG}And now I can feel that that happened
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.39,0:47:48.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我却希望时间能停下来\N{\rENG}and I want everything to slow down.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.47,0:47:49.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,很奇怪 在我的一生当中\N{\rENG}It's strange I've always had
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.74,0:47:52.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,这种感觉始终挥之不去\N{\rENG}this feeling no matter where I am in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.16,0:47:54.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,既像是真实存在 又仿佛南柯一梦\N{\rENG}That it's either a memory or a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.19,0:47:56.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道你一直有这种感觉\N{\rENG}I know you've always thought that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.31,0:47:58.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也是 就好像 这真的是我的人生吗\N{\rENG}Me too, it's like is this really my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.61,0:48:00.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在这一切都正在发生吗\N{\rENG}Like is it happening, right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.45,0:48:02.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 就是这样  - 我知道\N{\rENG}- It is.  - I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.55,0:48:04.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,每一年 我都会感受到\N{\rENG}Every year I just seem to get
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.91,0:48:06.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,更大的压力和打击\N{\rENG}a little bit more humbled and more overwhelmed
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.06,0:48:08.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,那些事情我从来搞不明白\N{\rENG}about all things I'm never gonna know or understand
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.64,0:48:09.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就是我一直在告诫你的\N{\rENG}That's what I keep telling you:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.61,0:48:10.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,你一无所知\N{\rENG}You know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.32,0:48:12.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道 我已经醒悟了\N{\rENG}I know, I know! I'm coming around!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.66,0:48:14.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,其实 一无所知并没有你想象的那么糟糕\N{\rENG}But not knowing is not so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.60,0:48:15.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说\N{\rENG}I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.86,0:48:19.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,关键是要不断发现 寻找\N{\rENG}The point is to be looking, searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.07,0:48:20.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,保持如饥似渴的状态\N{\rENG}to stay hungry, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.21,0:48:22.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 我只是希望能变得简单一点\N{\rENG}That's true... I just wish it was a little easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.66,0:48:24.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么意思\N{\rENG}How do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.36,0:48:27.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道的 就是保持一定的热情\N{\rENG}Just to maintain a certain level of passion, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.26,0:48:29.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有的一切都那么顺理成章\N{\rENG}I mean, it used to come so naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.05,0:48:32.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,记得我年轻的时候 我的一群作家朋友们\N{\rENG}Remember when I was younger, me and all my writer friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.68,0:48:35.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们可以感觉到自己在做的是重要的事情\N{\rENG}We like.. we just felt like were doing something important.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.53,0:48:37.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗 就好像是属于我们的时代\N{\rENG}You know? Like this was our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.20,0:48:40.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,可他们都是些骄傲自大的小子 对吗\N{\rENG}But they were all a bunch of arrogant little pricks, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.03,0:48:42.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 好吧 也许吧 我也不知道\N{\rENG}No! Alright, maybe... I dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.31,0:48:44.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们长大后就渐渐失去了\N{\rENG}we just grew out of all this energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.02,0:48:47.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,当初的热情 创造力和雄心壮志\N{\rENG}all this creativity or whatever ambitions people had.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.96,0:48:52.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得人还是应该年少轻狂些才好\N{\rENG}I think you gotta be a little deluded to stay motivated.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.15,0:48:55.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,年轻人都是这样 不停地把自己和别人比较\N{\rENG}Young men have this thing about comparing themselves all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.38,0:48:58.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们有很多自我评判的准绳\N{\rENG}They have all these signposts they judge themselves by.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.78,0:48:59.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,你以前也是这样\N{\rENG}You used to do that all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.88,0:49:00.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我怎么了 你什么意思\N{\rENG}Do what? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.91,0:49:03.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,像巴尔扎克十七岁创作出这部作品\N{\rENG}It's like Balzac wrote this by 17,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.80,0:49:05.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,而斯科特 ·菲茨杰拉德三十岁才写出来\N{\rENG}F. Scott Fitzgerald did this by 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.09,0:49:07.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,巴尔扎克每天早餐前创作一部作品\N{\rENG}And Balzac wrote a book before breakfast everyday.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.30,0:49:10.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 可是女人们并不这么想\N{\rENG}Yeah, but women do not think that way as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.48,0:49:11.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,你这么认为吗\N{\rENG}You don't think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.65,0:49:14.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们只是没什么可比的罢了\N{\rENG}We have much less to compare ourselves to, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.51,0:49:16.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,大多数有所成就的女人\N{\rENG}Most women who achieve anything in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.78,0:49:18.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,在你第一次听说她们时 都已经五十多岁了\N{\rENG}the first time you hear about them, they're in their 50s.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.95,0:49:19.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为在这以前 对女人来说\N{\rENG}because it is was so hard
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.87,0:49:22.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,想要得到一定的社会地位实在是太难了\N{\rENG}for them to get any recognitions before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.29,0:49:23.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,她们要么苦苦奋斗了三十年\N{\rENG}They struggled for 30 years
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.93,0:49:26.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,要么就是在能做自己想做的事之前\N{\rENG}or they raised kids and were stranded at home
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.74,0:49:28.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,都被困在家里 相夫教子\N{\rENG}before they could do what they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.73,0:49:32.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗 这其实也算是一种解放\N{\rENG}Actually you know what? It's kind of freeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.54,0:49:33.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们不用每天忙着去和马丁·路德·金\N{\rENG}We don't have to spend our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.81,0:49:38.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,圣雄甘地 托尔斯泰这些人去比较\N{\rENG}comparing ourselves to Martin Luther King, Ghandi, Tolstoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.01,0:49:39.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,那圣女贞德呢\N{\rENG}What about Joan of Arc?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.32,0:49:42.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说 她一个小姑娘却拯救了法国\N{\rENG}I mean... she was a teenager and she saved France.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.84,0:49:45.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁愿意做圣女贞德 忘记法国吧\N{\rENG}Who wants to be Joan of Arc? Forget France.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.55,0:49:48.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,她被绑在火刑柱上活活烧死 还是处女呢\N{\rENG}She was burned at the stake, and a virgin!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.35,0:49:51.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可不想这样 好吗 多伟大的情操\N{\rENG}Ok? Nothing I aspire to. What a great achievement!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.74,0:49:57.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 天哪  - 怎么了  - 没什么\N{\rENG}- Oh God...  - What?  - No, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.60,0:49:59.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 怎么了  - 这太奇怪了\N{\rENG}- What?  - This is so weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.48,0:50:06.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 什么意思  - 就像这样 我们边走边聊\N{\rENG}- What do you mean?  - Just this, us walking, having a conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.99,0:50:10.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,讨论一切和饮食工作无关的话题\N{\rENG}About something else than scheduling food, work.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.20,0:50:10.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,自从为一些鸡毛蒜皮的事劳心后\N{\rENG}I mean how long has it been
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.99,0:50:13.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们确实很久没有像现在这样了\N{\rENG}since we were wondering around bullshiting
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.44,0:50:16.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,我听到了什么 你能听到吗\N{\rENG}Do you hear what I hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.07,0:50:19.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 大海的声音吗  - 不\N{\rENG}- The sea?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.25,0:50:22.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么 我知道了 没琐事牵绊的声音\N{\rENG}What? Oh! No small feat.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.12,0:50:25.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有什么被推翻 没有什么需要清理\N{\rENG}Nothing being knocked over, nothing we have clean up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.73,0:50:27.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,也没有什么不公正的事情发生\N{\rENG}Nothing injustices being done.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.96,0:50:30.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,对啊 上一次是什么时候呢\N{\rENG}Yeah, so when was the last time?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.59,0:50:33.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,当我们无处可去的时候\N{\rENG}When we had nowhere to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.10,0:50:37.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊 还记得我们在卢森堡公园吗\N{\rENG}Yeah. Remember walking around the Luxembourg Gardens?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.39,0:50:39.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在混凝土乒乓球桌上把你打得落花流水\N{\rENG}I used to kick your ass in ping-pong on those concrete tables
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.91,0:50:42.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,恭喜你 竟然打赢了个怀着双胞胎的孕妇\N{\rENG}Congrats! You beat a woman pregnant with twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.95,0:50:43.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,真够男人的\N{\rENG}Such a gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.83,0:50:46.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,这总比输给一个怀着双胞胎的孕妇要好\N{\rENG}It is better than losing to a pregnant woman with twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.03,0:50:47.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 天哪\N{\rENG}Yes... O God!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.27,0:50:49.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我在想什么吗 我在想\N{\rENG}You know what I think? I think
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.30,0:50:52.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,从我们离开父母的那一刻起\N{\rENG}it's from the time we leave our parents' house,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.77,0:50:54.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,直到我们有了孩子\N{\rENG}until we have kids, that's the only time
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.73,0:50:56.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,只有那时 你的生活是完全属于你自己的\N{\rENG}that your life is completely your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.88,0:50:59.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,那种日子大概过了十年 真的很好\N{\rENG}I think I had about a decade of that, it was great, it was like,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.63,0:51:02.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像是一次漫长的流浪 每一天\N{\rENG}just like one long flowing, a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.61,0:51:04.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,一星期 一年 都没有太大的区别\N{\rENG}a week, a year, there wasn't much difference
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.94,0:51:07.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是 我过去总是把时间\N{\rENG}No... I know, I used to keep track of time
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.13,0:51:09.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,花在工作和男朋友们的身上\N{\rENG}through jobs and boyfriends and stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.91,0:51:10.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在我却可以说出\N{\rENG}Now I can tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.81,0:51:13.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,在过去的七年中\N{\rENG}every detail of the past seven years
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.28,0:51:15.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,孩子们身上发生过的每一件小事\N{\rENG}based on what was happening in the girls' lives
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.14,0:51:16.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 没错\N{\rENG}Yeah...right... totally.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.50,0:51:19.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你也是吗  - 是的\N{\rENG}- You do that too?  - Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.43,0:51:21.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说 如果真的把时间划分开\N{\rENG}if, I mean, time is demarcated now
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.03,0:51:25.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 真不敢相信 你竟然也记得\N{\rENG}No, I'm just surprised you do that too
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.07,0:51:27.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 来个小测验\N{\rENG}Ok... quick test
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.45,0:51:29.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,二〇〇九年八月\N{\rENG}August 2009.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.49,0:51:33.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,来吧 考考你 那时发生了什么\N{\rENG}No, come on! It's a quick one. What was happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.33,0:51:36.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,二〇〇九年八月 我们在和你父母度假\N{\rENG}August 2009, we were on vacation with your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.96,0:51:39.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,妮娜先起了水痘 紧接着就是艾拉\N{\rENG}Nina got the chickenpox first and quickly followed by Ella
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.89,0:51:43.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真没想到  - 可以奖励我一颗五角星了吗\N{\rENG}- I am so impressed.  - So do I get a gold star?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.69,0:51:44.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,可以考虑\N{\rENG}Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.36,0:51:49.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我能问你一个问题吗  - 当然了\N{\rENG}- Hey... can I ask you a question?  - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.16,0:51:51.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果我们今天第一次在火车上邂逅\N{\rENG}If we were meeting for the first time today on a train,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.46,0:51:53.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,你会被我吸引吗\N{\rENG}would you find me attractive?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.86,0:51:56.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 当然了  - 不 我是说我现在这个样子\N{\rENG}- Of course.  - No, but really right now as I am
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.74,0:51:59.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,你会开始和我搭讪吗\N{\rENG}Would you start talking to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.24,0:52:01.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,你会邀请我和你一起下火车吗\N{\rENG}Would you ask me to get off the train with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.47,0:52:06.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的这些问题都是些假设\N{\rENG}I mean you're asking a theoretical question.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.17,0:52:08.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只想知道我的人生会是怎样\N{\rENG}I mean what would my life-situation be?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.15,0:52:09.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,从理论上来讲 它不会欺骗你吗\N{\rENG}Technically, it would not be cheating on you?
