Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.58,0:53:15.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 当然不会了 还有人在等我呢\N{\rENG}No, of course not, I have people waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.11,0:53:20.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道的 一只四十一岁还在发情的雄性山羊\N{\rENG}You know, and a 41-year-old horny billy goat
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.06,0:53:22.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,太吓人了 我能起一身鸡皮疙瘩 救命啊\N{\rENG}How creepy! I'm creeped out right now. Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.97,0:53:23.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,救命啊{\rZHU}[希腊语]\N{\rENG}Βοήθεια
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.85,0:53:25.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,真不敢相信 我都四十一了\N{\rENG}I can not believe I'm 41.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.92,0:53:28.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也不敢相信 你竟然都这么老了\N{\rENG}Yeah, me neither. You've gotten so old.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.54,0:53:30.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没想过自己会和一个四十多岁的人睡在一起\N{\rENG}Never thought I would ever sleep with anyone over 40
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.37,0:53:31.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rENG}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.15,0:53:32.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗\N{\rENG}Actually you know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.02,0:53:33.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是和我睡过的人当中年纪最大的一个\N{\rENG}You are the oldest guy I've ever slept with.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.76,0:53:35.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这样啊  - 是真的\N{\rENG}- That is something  - That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.09,0:53:37.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道 不过我可不是你拒绝的最老的家伙\N{\rENG}I know, but I'm not the oldest guy you've ever blown
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.55,0:53:41.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 什么  - 那次在华沙的会议\N{\rENG}- What!  - That conference in Warsaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.62,0:53:44.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 什么会议  - 瓦文萨\N{\rENG}- What conference?  - Lech Walesa.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.52,0:53:48.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,瓦文萨 你在说什么呢\N{\rENG}Lech Walesa! Oh what are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.32,0:53:50.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,没关系 那都是我们在一起以前的事了\N{\rENG}It's ok, it was before we're together
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.19,0:53:54.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,没什么不敢承认的 我还记得你提起过他\N{\rENG}You can admit it. I can remember the way you talked about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.30,0:53:56.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,他是如何让你打开心扉\N{\rENG}How he opened your heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.04,0:53:57.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,你明确地拒绝了他\N{\rENG}you definitely blew him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.32,0:53:59.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 你真是疯了\N{\rENG}Ok... you're really crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.84,0:54:01.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是戈尔巴乔夫\N{\rENG}That was Gorbachev.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.23,0:54:03.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 你这个地理不通\N{\rENG}Ok? Geographically challenged,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.64,0:54:06.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,痴迷橄榄球又爱吃甜甜圈的美国佬\N{\rENG}football-obsessed, doughnut-loving American.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.22,0:54:07.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是戈尔巴乔夫\N{\rENG}That was Gorbachev.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.01,0:54:09.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,不好意思 我总搞不清东方国家的这些领袖\N{\rENG}I'm sorry I got Eastern-bloc leaders mixed up, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.42,0:54:12.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没有拒绝他 好吗 收回你的话\N{\rENG}And I did not blow him, ok? Take it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.36,0:54:13.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 好吧\N{\rENG}Ok, ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.56,0:54:14.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,天哪\N{\rENG}God!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.21,0:54:18.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以那是戈尔巴乔夫\N{\rENG}So was it Gorbachev?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.52,0:54:20.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 你知道的\N{\rENG}All right, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.17,0:54:23.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,听着 我本来打算一会儿再跟你说\N{\rENG}Listen to this... I was going to wait
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.91,0:54:28.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,可我这个人就是藏不住话\N{\rENG}to tell you this till later, but I'm so bad with secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.02,0:54:28.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.33,0:54:30.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,你脑子里长了肿瘤 快死了吗\N{\rENG}You've got a tumor in your brain and you are going to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.23,0:54:31.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 不是\N{\rENG}No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.34,0:54:32.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是这些 好吗\N{\rENG}Nothing like that, alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.80,0:54:35.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 其实也有点像\N{\rENG}Well, actually, it's kind of like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.42,0:54:38.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我祖母死了  - 不是吧 什么时候的事\N{\rENG}- My grandmother died.  - What! When?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.45,0:54:41.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 我们吃饭前我爸爸发短信告诉我的\N{\rENG}Yes, my dad texted to me right before we ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.10,0:54:43.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,对不起 你怎么不早说\N{\rENG}Oh I'm so sorry. Why didn't you tell me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.45,0:54:45.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,像每个人都希望的那样\N{\rENG}Everyone has been expecting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.03,0:54:46.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,她活得够长了 而且一生幸福\N{\rENG}she has lived a long time, had a great life.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.93,0:54:48.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,她九十六岁了\N{\rENG}She was 96.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.29,0:54:51.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,你祖父死后没多久 她就去世了\N{\rENG}She did not live much longer after your grandfather died.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.44,0:54:53.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 有一年了\N{\rENG}No... barely a year...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.27,0:54:56.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,有趣的是 这女人还是个奇怪的圣人\N{\rENG}The funny thing is that this woman was a freaking saint, ok?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.97,0:55:00.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,战争时期 她做过护士 照顾我们所有人\N{\rENG}She was a nurse in the war. She took care of all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.24,0:55:03.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,她从来没有说过别人一句坏话\N{\rENG}You know... she never said any unkind word about anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.64,0:55:05.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 真希望我能遇到她  - 没关系的\N{\rENG}- I wish I had met her.  - It's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.39,0:55:07.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 因为到后来\N{\rENG}Okay, because by the end, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.58,0:55:09.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,她不想再认识任何人了\N{\rENG}she just was not really into meeting new people.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.48,0:55:12.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,一辈子都在笑面以对\N{\rENG}I mean after a lifetime of being sweet as a pie,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.28,0:55:16.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,自从祖父死后 她受到了很大的打击\N{\rENG}once grandpa died, she got kind of awry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.19,0:55:18.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,是吗 那时她还在服丧吧\N{\rENG}Really? It happens, she was in mourning, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.37,0:55:21.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 我父亲说她一直在等死\N{\rENG}Yeah, well, my dad said she was just waiting to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.56,0:55:24.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们结婚多久了\N{\rENG}How long were they married?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.20,0:55:25.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,七十四年了\N{\rENG}74 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.82,0:55:29.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,靠 怎么可能\N{\rENG}Fuck! How is that even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.90,0:55:33.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,要是我们也一起生活七十四年 那得多老啊\N{\rENG}How old will we be if we were together for 74 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.57,0:55:36.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,那我们要从什么时候开始算起\N{\rENG}Hm, when do we start counting from?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.95,0:55:40.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想应该从我们第一次发生关系时算起吧\N{\rENG}I guess from the first time we had sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.01,0:55:41.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Ok...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.11,0:55:44.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,那应该是一九九四年\N{\rENG}OK, so... 1994.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.63,0:55:50.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 一九九四年 那还有五十六年\N{\rENG}Ok... 1994... 56 years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.38,0:55:52.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,那时我们都九十八岁了\N{\rENG}We will be 98.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.66,0:55:55.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,天哪 你还能\N{\rENG}Oh! Would you be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.80,0:55:57.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,再忍受我整整五十六年吗\N{\rENG}put up with me for another 56 more years?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.69,0:55:59.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,我得搞清楚 我不知道自己\N{\rENG}I need to know. I do not know
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.19,0:56:01.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,是不是还能忍你那么长时间\N{\rENG}if I'm gonna be able to put up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.45,0:56:04.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你想想他们见证的那些变化 真不可思议\N{\rENG}It's crazy if you think about all the change they saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.00,0:56:06.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,当他们见到彼此已经没有了最初的感觉\N{\rENG}I mean, when they met, neither one of them had electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.93,0:56:09.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,他过去常常骑马带她上学\N{\rENG}He used to take her to school on his horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.52,0:56:13.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,毕业时他们两个分别是致辞的学生代表\N{\rENG}When he graduated, he was valedictorian and she was salutatorian.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.35,0:56:16.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 什么意思  - 祖父第一名 祖母第二名\N{\rENG}- What is that?  - He was top of the class and she was second.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.90,0:56:18.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,我敢说一定是祖母故意放水\N{\rENG}I bet she knowingly got a couple of answers wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.93,0:56:20.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,你祖父才会轻松拿到第一\N{\rENG}so that he did not feel threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.51,0:56:22.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果她想轻松一点 这就是最好的办法\N{\rENG}Well, if she wanted to get laid, she'd better have.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.86,0:56:25.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 你知道 有人就是这么做的\N{\rENG}Yes, obviously like you know who.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.22,0:56:26.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,不管怎么说 在收到短信之后\N{\rENG}Anyway, so I called my dad, right,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.76,0:56:28.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,我告诉我爸爸\N{\rENG}after I got the text, just, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.60,0:56:30.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很遗憾\N{\rENG}to tell him I was sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.33,0:56:33.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想我可能说错了一些话\N{\rENG}I think I got screwed up at some point said...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.13,0:56:37.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,爸爸 你现在是孤儿了 我觉得这不好笑\N{\rENG}Hey, dad, you're an orphan now, I don't think it was funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.00,0:56:39.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 一点都不好笑  - 好吧 好像是不好笑\N{\rENG}- Not funny at all  - Yeah, I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.94,0:56:41.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 下一个是他 之后就是你  - 我知道\N{\rENG}- He's next, then you.  - I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.65,0:56:44.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,他告诉我说 我的祖父母\N{\rENG}Well... he told me that my grandparents
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.18,0:56:45.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,想要死后葬在一起\N{\rENG}wanted to have a joint service.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.93,0:56:49.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们希望两人的骨灰能埋在一起\N{\rENG}They wanted to have their ashes intermingled and be buried as one.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.69,0:56:51.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,你祖父没有办葬礼吗\N{\rENG}Your grandfather didn't have a funeral?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.09,0:56:52.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们彼此立誓\N{\rENG}They vowed to each other
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.50,0:56:54.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,绝不去参加对方的葬礼\N{\rENG}they'd never have to attend one another's funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.09,0:56:57.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 我更希望你能参加我的葬礼\N{\rENG}Oh yeah... I kind of like the idea of you attending mine.
