Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.84,0:57:59.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,这地方让我想起了\N{\rENG}Wow, this place reminds me
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.43,0:58:01.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我小时候看过的一部电影\N{\rENG}a bit of a movie I saw when I was a teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.91,0:58:05.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是一部五十年代的黑白片\N{\rENG}It was a black and white film from the 50s.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.04,0:58:07.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得 有一对夫妇走在庞贝古城的废墟旁\N{\rENG}I remember a couple walking through the ruins of Pompeii,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.84,0:58:10.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,看着那些在那里躺了好几个世纪的尸骸\N{\rENG}viewing bodies that had been lying there for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.86,0:58:12.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还记得那些尸骸\N{\rENG}I remember the bodies, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.58,0:58:15.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们在睡梦中被捕的时候还紧拥着爱人\N{\rENG}caught in their sleep still lovingly holding each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.45,0:58:19.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也不知道为什么 有时候我经常在想\N{\rENG}I don't know why, sometimes I have this image in my mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.96,0:58:22.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,你搂着我 我们躺在一起\N{\rENG}where, you know, we're asleep and you hold me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.57,0:58:24.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,在炽热的灰烬下被活活掩埋\N{\rENG}What... of being buried alive under molten ash?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.75,0:58:26.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你就是在想这些吗  - 是的\N{\rENG}- That's what you're thinking about?  - Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.80,0:58:28.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,这可一点都不好玩\N{\rENG}That's not very fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.52,0:58:31.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道 其实也没那么可怕\N{\rENG}I don't know... It's not horrible I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.73,0:58:34.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们当中 有些夫妇中间还躺着孩子\N{\rENG}they had some bodies with little kids sleeping between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.49,0:58:35.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,那很好\N{\rENG}That's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.05,0:58:37.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊 我想我年轻的时候有些病态\N{\rENG}Yeah, I guess I was young and a bit morbid,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.84,0:58:40.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,觉得和自己心爱的人死在一起是很浪漫的事\N{\rENG}I mean at that age you romanticize dying with the person you love.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.87,0:58:42.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,那现在你愿意和我一起死吗\N{\rENG}Now you want to die with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.98,0:58:45.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,也许吧 你知道 如果是\N{\rENG}Maybe you know if you were... you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.84,0:58:48.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们在一起的第一个晚上 也许会\N{\rENG}our first night together then,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.11,0:58:50.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,可那是好久以前了 现在我才不\N{\rENG}a long time ago, but now... no!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.15,0:58:51.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想活着\N{\rENG}I'd like to live!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.07,0:58:53.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也只是想来点浪漫的 也被你破坏了\N{\rENG}I just wanted you to say something romantic and you blew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.54,0:58:56.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,算了吧 去你妈的 我搞砸了\N{\rENG}Oh no! Putain de merde. I blew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.80,0:58:59.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,等我们都九十八岁了 你可以再问一次\N{\rENG}Ok, if we are both 98, you can ask me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.08,0:59:00.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过现在\N{\rENG}But any time sooner,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.37,0:59:04.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,对不起了\N{\rENG}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.44,0:59:06.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就是我说过的那个拜占庭时期\N{\rENG}Hey... This is the chapel I was telling you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.82,0:59:09.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,就有了的小教堂 已经有一千年历史了\N{\rENG}It's from the Byzantine era, like a 1000 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.40,0:59:12.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我们能进去吗  - 当然能了\N{\rENG}- Can we go in?  - Yes, I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.90,0:59:16.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,来看看 有人吗\N{\rENG}Check this out! Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.34,0:59:23.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是圣奥蒂莉亚的神龛 她是视力的守护神\N{\rENG}It's a shrine to St. Odilia, the patron saint to eyesight.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.09,0:59:24.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,人们从各处前来\N{\rENG}People come from all over
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.07,0:59:26.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,给盲人留下各种小贡品\N{\rENG}and they leave little dedications to the blind
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.25,0:59:28.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,帮助他们恢复视力\N{\rENG}to help restore sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.81,0:59:30.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,一定很灵吧\N{\rENG}I'm sure, it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.61,0:59:32.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,这里的这些画\N{\rENG}And these paitings here,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.31,0:59:34.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我联想到日本的和尚\N{\rENG}they make me think of those Japanese monks, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.92,0:59:36.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有他们的无常思想\N{\rENG}with their deal on impermanence?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.47,0:59:39.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,天热时 他们喜欢用水在石头上画画\N{\rENG}They like to paint with water on rock on hot days
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.09,0:59:41.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以画完的时候 就都蒸发了\N{\rENG}so by the time they're done it's already evaporated.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.22,0:59:44.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,眼睛被挖掉了 是和失明有关吗\N{\rENG}Oh, the eyes are scratched out is that about blindness?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.78,0:59:45.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 我本来也那么想\N{\rENG}No, I thought that too,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.90,0:59:47.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是那个看守人\N{\rENG}but the caretaker guy
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.97,0:59:52.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,他告诉我 是土耳其人占领的时候干的\N{\rENG}he told me that the Turks did that during the occupation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.23,0:59:55.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 我再也不吃土耳其食物了\N{\rENG}That's it. I'm never eating Turkish food again.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.95,0:59:57.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Oh, ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.18,0:59:59.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,那会让整个国际社会为之一颤的\N{\rENG}That will send a shiver through international community.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.52,1:00:02.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 那我再也不给土耳其人吹箫了\N{\rENG}OK, fine. Then I will never suck another turkish cock.
