Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.40,1:10:45.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,和你妈妈相处愉快\N{\rENG}"Good luck with your mom."
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.34,1:10:47.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 拜托  - 我可没别的意思\N{\rENG}- I mean, c'mon...  - I  didn't mean anything by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.78,1:10:49.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道 但这样不好\N{\rENG}I know, but it's not good.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.21,1:10:50.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,这样又让他想起了整件事情\N{\rENG}You know, it just reminds him of the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.64,1:10:51.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真希望你别那样\N{\rENG}and I wish you wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.67,1:10:53.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,你以为我不说他就忘了吗\N{\rENG}Oh, like you think he forgets?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.33,1:10:54.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,真是典型的美式思维\N{\rENG}That's so American
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.13,1:10:56.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,掩盖事实 当做从未发生\N{\rENG}to just swipe it under the carpet and act as if it didn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.67,1:10:58.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说 为什么要让他想起来呢\N{\rENG}Why put it into his head, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.45,1:11:01.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,或许他这会儿不想去想这件事呢\N{\rENG}What if he does not want to think about it right now?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.64,1:11:04.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不会有影响的  - 会有一点 会的\N{\rENG}- It means nothing.  - It means something. It does.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.97,1:11:06.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 前些天我还和他开了个玩笑\N{\rENG}Alright, I even made a joke the other day
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.73,1:11:07.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,说我和他妈妈应该\N{\rENG}that his mom and I should try
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.97,1:11:10.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,来一场泥地大摔跤 才能一决胜负\N{\rENG}to settle it in one big mud wrestling contest.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.69,1:11:13.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 泥地大摔跤 你真那么说了  - 他笑了\N{\rENG}- Mud wrestling? You said that?  - And he laughed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.47,1:11:15.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,或许他比你要有幽默感\N{\rENG}He might have more of a sense of humour than you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.42,1:11:16.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,拜托\N{\rENG}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.47,1:11:18.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们刚说过的\N{\rENG}I dunno, we just talked about that,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.08,1:11:19.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,你说他妈妈坏话的时候\N{\rENG}you know, when you say bad things about his mom
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.78,1:11:21.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,他听见的是自己的坏话\N{\rENG}what he hears is bad things about himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.73,1:11:24.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可没说他妈妈坏话 我开个玩笑而已\N{\rENG}Well I didn't say anything bad about his mom, ok? I made a joke.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.16,1:11:26.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,开的不光是她的玩笑 也是我自己的\N{\rENG}It's as much on me as much as it is on her.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.35,1:11:30.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道 我知道 只是 根本没必要提\N{\rENG}I know, I know. It's just why conjure it up at all, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.76,1:11:32.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得他现在够大了\N{\rENG}I think he's old enough now.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.43,1:11:35.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,他知道他妈妈和我之间是怎么回事\N{\rENG}I mean, he knows how bad it is between his mother and I.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.76,1:11:37.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是他妈妈和我  - 我什么也没做\N{\rENG}- His mom and me.  - And I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.75,1:11:39.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,都是她冲着我来的\N{\rENG}It's all coming from her towards me.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.51,1:11:43.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,她恨我 没错 很久前我睡了她男人\N{\rENG}OK, she hates me. Yes. I fucked her husband a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.36,1:11:45.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者是不是该说 他睡了我\N{\rENG}Or should I say he fucked me?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.73,1:11:46.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊 没错\N{\rENG}Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.92,1:11:48.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,他妈妈和我本来就不和\N{\rENG}Ok, making a joke about the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.75,1:11:51.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,拿这开个玩笑 没什么大不了的\N{\rENG}that his mother and I do not love each other is not the issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.45,1:11:53.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,他不会因为这样就受到创伤\N{\rENG}That's not going to traumatize him.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.08,1:11:54.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为他已经受伤了 好吗\N{\rENG}That already happened, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.68,1:11:57.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在你想转移你的负罪感给我吗\N{\rENG}And now you are trying to transfer your guilt and blame me?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.44,1:11:58.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.02,1:12:01.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,知道吗 反过来 如果你能一笑了之\N{\rENG}You know, on the contrary, if you can make a joke about it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.15,1:12:02.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,或许你就能好受点\N{\rENG}maybe you'll be able to live with it better.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.64,1:12:04.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我是这么想的  - 好吧\N{\rENG}- That's what I think.  - OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.29,1:12:06.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,你说得对 一如既往\N{\rENG}You're right, as always.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.85,1:12:08.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们别说这个了 好吗\N{\rENG}Let's just not talk about it, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.73,1:12:11.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,他妈妈要是个醉鬼\N{\rENG}It's nobody's fault if his mom
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.65,1:12:13.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者虐待狂 可怨不得任何人\N{\rENG}is drunk and abusive psychologically.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.95,1:12:15.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,别那么说\N{\rENG}Don't say that!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.74,1:12:18.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,他得和她一起生活 想到这我就恶心\N{\rENG}I mean it makes me sick that he has to be with her
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.17,1:12:21.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我想 法官会认为女人都有母性吧\N{\rENG}but I guess judges assume that women have the mother instinct.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.54,1:12:24.37,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}美狄亚{\u0}：希腊神话中科尔喀斯国王之女，以巫术著称\N{\rCHS}她的母性就和美狄亚差不多\N{\rENG}She has the mother instinct of Medea!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.66,1:12:26.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,美狄亚吗\N{\rENG}Medea, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.08,1:12:27.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊 那不过是个希腊神话\N{\rENG}Yeah, after all it is a Greek myth.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.76,1:12:29.92,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}欧里庇得斯{\u0}：希腊悲剧诗人\N{\rCHS}其实是欧里庇得斯的剧作\N{\rENG}Actually, a play by Euripides.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.42,1:12:33.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个女人 为惩罚前夫不惜杀死孩子\N{\rENG}A woman killing her kids to punish her ex-husband,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.30,1:12:34.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,她和这没什么两样\N{\rENG}that's basically what she's doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.45,1:12:36.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,她是在伤害他来报复你\N{\rENG}She's hurting him to get to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.06,1:12:38.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 她是利用他来破坏我的生活\N{\rENG}No, she's making my life hell through him.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.63,1:12:39.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,这才是她所做的\N{\rENG}That's what she's doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.96,1:12:44.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,但有时候 你说的话太过分了\N{\rENG}But sometimes you say things that just go too far.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.19,1:12:46.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,行了 别把你老婆的这个闹剧里\N{\rENG}Ok, stop blaming me for everything that is wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.36,1:12:48.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有的问题都怪在我身上 好吗\N{\rENG}in this whole thing with your wife, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.02,1:12:51.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是前妻 很久以前就是前妻了  - 好吧\N{\rENG}- Ex-wife! Ex-wife for a long time!  - OK,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.16,1:12:52.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,你当初就应该处理得好一点\N{\rENG}you should have dealt better with it a little better back then,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.82,1:12:54.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,她就不会这么恨我们了\N{\rENG}she wouldn't have hated us so much, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.83,1:12:57.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,好 好 是我搞砸了\N{\rENG}OK, ok, I screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.55,1:13:00.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,你真是厉害 我们生活中\N{\rENG}Alright. I just love this little rewrite you do that
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.67,1:13:04.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,有什么不如意 你都能说成是我的错\N{\rENG}everything that isn't perfect in our life gets laid at my feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.53,1:13:07.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在你要因为亨利 给我扣这种帽子吗\N{\rENG}Now you're putting this shit on me about Henry?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.34,1:13:10.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么帽子 你说什么呢\N{\rENG}What shit? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.76,1:13:12.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我来告诉你我在说什么吧\N{\rENG}Let me tell you what I am talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.44,1:13:15.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,你这是要我搬去芝加哥 放弃我的生活\N{\rENG}The moving to Chicago and giving up my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.03,1:13:19.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,你说亨利需要你\N{\rENG}Now that you mentioned that Henry needs you
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.45,1:13:21.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我什么感受吗\N{\rENG}how do you think that makes me feel?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.41,1:13:23.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很痛苦 知道吗\N{\rENG}I'm miserable, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.60,1:13:26.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还怎么接受那份工作 你告诉我\N{\rENG}How can I take that job now? Tell me, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.63,1:13:27.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我会有负罪感的  - 别这样\N{\rENG}- I'll feel too guilty.  - No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.89,1:13:30.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不行不行  - 那是你自己选择\N{\rENG}- No, no, no, no.  - That's a choice you're making
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.03,1:13:31.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,要这样看待它的 明白吗\N{\rENG}to look at it like that, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.51,1:13:35.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,女人就应该做养育者 这是天性\N{\rENG}It is in the nature of women to be the nurturer.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.75,1:13:36.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rENG}The what?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.79,1:13:39.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 养育者  - 养育者\N{\rENG}- The nurturer.  - The nurturer?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.10,1:13:41.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 这个词我简直说不出口\N{\rENG}OK, I can't even say that fucking word.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.05,1:13:43.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就是本能地会对一切感到内疚\N{\rENG}I just naturally feel bad about everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.42,1:13:45.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,你还给我那种眼神 好像是我的错\N{\rENG}And you give me that look like it's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.66,1:13:46.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么眼神\N{\rENG}What look?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.45,1:13:49.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是怪我忘了把项目报告放进包里的眼神\N{\rENG}That I forget to put in the bag the science project look.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.34,1:13:51.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我知道你怪我  - 我什么也没说\N{\rENG}- I know you blame me.  - I didn't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.62,1:13:54.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,对 你是什么也没说 你不用说出来\N{\rENG}No, you did not say anything. You didn't have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.07,1:13:57.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 错的从来都是我  - 好吧\N{\rENG}- Yeah, it's always my fault.  - Yeah right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.90,1:13:59.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我上班时在冰箱上看到\N{\rENG}I read on the fridge at work,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.97,1:14:03.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,那种用来拼句子的 贴在磁铁上的单词\N{\rENG}you know those magnet words that people make sentences with.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.23,1:14:05.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,有人拼了这么个句子\N{\rENG}Someone had put together:
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.71,1:14:11.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,在牺牲的花园里 女人寻求着永生\N{\rENG}"Women explore for eternity in the vast garden of sacrifice."
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.34,1:14:15.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,这一定是上帝的指示吧\N{\rENG}Wow, that's a sure sign from God.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.71,1:14:18.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 这话真他妈是真理\N{\rENG}Yeah, that line is so damn true
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.03,1:14:19.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,过去一万年来都是\N{\rENG}and it’s been for 10,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.49,1:14:20.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,但到此为止\N{\rENG}But that's enough, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.93,1:14:22.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不想做这样的女人\N{\rENG}I don't want to be one of these women.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.59,1:14:24.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像结婚权对于同性恋\N{\rENG}Like marriage is important to gays,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.63,1:14:26.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,避孕对于维护女权的重要性\N{\rENG}or contraception to women rights.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.66,1:14:28.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,一旦我失去了信心\N{\rENG}It's the same with giving up my hopes,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.56,1:14:29.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,对于无数妇女\N{\rENG}with the millions of women
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.64,1:14:30.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也不得不放弃她们的希望\N{\rENG}that I have had to give up their hopes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.96,1:14:31.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不会这样的\N{\rENG}I'm not gonna do it!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.97,1:14:34.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,这不是我一个人的事情\N{\rENG}This is bigger than me, this means more than me.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.07,1:14:42.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,真精彩 连诺贝尔委员会都注意到了\N{\rENG}Wow, bravo, the Nobel Committee is taking note, and just...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.99,1:14:45.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,等下 我去通知一下瑞典方面 好吧\N{\rENG}Hold on a second, I'm going to alert Sweden, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.30,1:14:47.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,面对如此多的女性压迫问题\N{\rENG}I mean... it must be a full-time job
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.53,1:14:48.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,你一定是身负重任\N{\rENG}carrying that much feminine oppression.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.91,1:14:51.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没错  - 遭受了这么多\N{\rENG}- It is.  - You suffered so much,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.20,1:14:52.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,在巴黎中产阶级家庭长大\N{\rENG}growing up in middle class Paris,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.70,1:14:54.70,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}后女性主义{\u0}：上世纪九十年代女性追求性认同的主义\N{\rCHS}在后女性主义者时期\N{\rENG}I mean the agony in the trenches
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.70,1:14:56.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,因索邦主义而苦恼\N{\rENG}of the Sorbonne in the post-feminist era.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.67,1:14:58.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,实在无法想像\N{\rENG}I can not imagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.03,1:14:59.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是个混蛋\N{\rENG}You're an asshole.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.72,1:15:00.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,知道吗 亲爱的\N{\rENG}You know what, sweetie?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.91,1:15:02.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,搬去芝加哥后\N{\rENG}When I move into Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.06,1:15:05.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一定要找到一套好房子\N{\rENG}I want to make sure we're able to find a nice house,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.95,1:15:07.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,缝制窗帘\N{\rENG}and I can sew the drapes,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.70,1:15:09.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,挑些搭配的床罩\N{\rENG}And pick matching bed covers...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.57,1:15:12.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,你今晚就打算这样度过吗\N{\rENG}So this is how you now want to be spending this evening?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.45,1:15:14.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,一直说这些吗\N{\rENG}I mean, this is, this is what you wanna do tonight?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.19,1:15:15.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你先开始的  - 不\N{\rENG}- Well, you started it.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.08,1:15:19.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,是你一直念叨个不停\N{\rENG}You're the one who will not shut up about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.05,1:15:22.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,但如果真心想说 我是说谈论什么\N{\rENG}But if you want to talk about it, I mean really talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.26,1:15:26.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,那就心平气和 理性地说\N{\rENG}I would prefer to have an unemotional, rational conversation.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.31,1:15:27.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,你觉得我们能做到吗\N{\rENG}I mean, do you think we could do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.37,1:15:29.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这可能吗  - 又开始了\N{\rENG}- Would that be possible?  - Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.56,1:15:31.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,要心平气和 要理性\N{\rENG}Unemotional, rational.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.38,1:15:34.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,你总是那个理智的人\N{\rENG}You always play the part of the one and only rational one.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.62,1:15:38.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我一直在不可理喻歇斯底里地闹\N{\rENG}And I'm the irrational, hysterical, hormone-crazy one,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.20,1:15:39.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,是因为我有感情\N{\rENG}because I have emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.63,1:15:42.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,是 你以旁观者从全局角度谈论问题\N{\rENG}Yeah, you sit back and you speak from your big perspective,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.68,1:15:45.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以你说出来的一定是经过冷静思考的\N{\rENG}which means everything you say is level-headed and true.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.30,1:15:47.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我也没有总是袖手旁观  - 整个世界\N{\rENG}- I don't always do anything.  - The world is fucked
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.43,1:15:50.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,都被冷静而理智的男人的决策给毁掉了\N{\rENG}by unemotional, irrational men deciding shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.49,1:15:53.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,政客无故就计划开战\N{\rENG}Alright? Politicians going to war for no reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.25,1:15:55.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,商业巨头要榨干能源\N{\rENG}corporate heads deciding to rape the environment.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.84,1:15:58.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,钱尼·拉姆斯菲尔德 多么理智的男人\N{\rENG}Chaney, Rumsfeld, very rational men.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.94,1:16:00.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,钱尼·拉姆斯菲尔德 那倒是\N{\rENG}Chaney, Rumsfeld, yeah, ok.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.61,1:16:02.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果我知道解决办法\N{\rENG}If I know a solution,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.45,1:16:04.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,一定是经过深思熟虑才决定的\N{\rENG}Very rational thinking behind it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.30,1:16:07.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我们现在是怎样 挑战最终解决方案\N{\rENG}Okay, so we are there now? Us versus the final solution.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.49,1:16:10.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,行 这样 回答我一个问题好吧\N{\rENG}Okay... let's do it, alright? Let me ask you this, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.54,1:16:13.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,你觉得亨利的生活\N{\rENG}Do you think Henry's life
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.62,1:16:16.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,会不会因为你我关系更为稳定\N{\rENG}would be helped by more consistent presence
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.08,1:16:17.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,而有所改善\N{\rENG}by you and me?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.10,1:16:19.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 又来了  - 不\N{\rENG}- Here we go.  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.08,1:16:21.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不罢休 那就好好来谈谈 行不\N{\rENG}You won't drop it. So let's talk about it. Alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.51,1:16:23.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就问你一句\N{\rENG}Let me just ask you one question.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.90,1:16:26.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,汉克会不会因为你我关系更为稳定\N{\rENG}Do you think Hank's life would be better served by
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.45,1:16:28.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,而在生活上得到更好的照顾\N{\rENG}more consistent presence from you and me?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.67,1:16:30.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然 他跟我们住一起会更好\N{\rENG}Yes! I think it would be better if he lived with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.86,1:16:31.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 对  - 而且他妈\N{\rENG}- Okay.  - And I think his mom
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.85,1:16:34.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,是个酗酒又讨厌的贱人\N{\rENG}is a fucking alcoholic, hateful cunt
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.40,1:16:36.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,利用我们在巴黎 我在生孩子的时间\N{\rENG}that used the time we were in Paris and I was giving birth,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.91,1:16:40.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,差点就把亨利合法驱逐出纽约\N{\rENG}and almost dying to legally move Henry out of New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.70,1:16:42.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,操丫的\N{\rENG}Fuck her!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.43,1:16:44.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,好 这我同意你\N{\rENG}Okay, I agree with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.70,1:16:47.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,虽然遗憾的是 我们不能让他离开美国\N{\rENG}Okay, unfortunately we can not go and get him out of America,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.97,1:16:50.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,但可以在想去见他的时候过去\N{\rENG}but we could if we wanted to go to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.92,1:16:53.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,虽然这是个大变动\N{\rENG}Now I know it would be a big move,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.41,1:16:54.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,但你还是考虑考虑如何\N{\rENG}but what do you think? I mean
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.22,1:16:57.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,在美国就真的找不到让你开心的事情吗\N{\rENG}is there any way that you could be happy in the US?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.83,1:17:00.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,难道去美国就是不可能的事情吗\N{\rENG}I mean is that just out of the realm of possibility?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.26,1:17:02.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,也可以找一份差不多的工作的 是不是\N{\rENG}I mean you could find a comparable job there?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.87,1:17:04.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 差不多的  - 对啊\N{\rENG}- Comparable job?  - Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.11,1:17:05.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你搞笑的吧  - 不\N{\rENG}- Are you kidding?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.64,1:17:07.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,为什么总让我来妥协\N{\rENG}Why am I the one that always have to make the compromises?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.74,1:17:08.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,天哪\N{\rENG}Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.66,1:17:11.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不应该是  - 别搞这么夸张 好吗\N{\rENG}- I mean it should be...  - Don't be so dramatic, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.46,1:17:13.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,我 反正要搬去芝加哥这事\N{\rENG}I... Well, moving to Chicago is
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.11,1:17:15.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 对我来说就是很夸张  - 我不是说\N{\rENG}- Pretty fucking dramatic to me.  - I'm not saying
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.69,1:17:18.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,就该搬过去 我只是想谈谈这可能性\N{\rENG}we should move. I just want to talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.60,1:17:21.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,你就不能淡定那么两秒钟 好好谈谈吗\N{\rENG}Can you be my friend for like two seconds so we can talk?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.17,1:17:22.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 行 就一会儿  - 好的\N{\rENG}- Okay, two seconds  - Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.50,1:17:23.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,记不记得你有一次\N{\rENG}Do you remember that time that you were like
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.94,1:17:25.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,去接女儿们 迟到了大概三十五分钟\N{\rENG}35 minutes late to pick up the girls from school,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.92,1:17:27.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,你当时紧张死了\N{\rENG}and you were so stressed out,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.39,1:17:29.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为你知道她们在操场上\N{\rENG}because you knew they were out there in the playground,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.08,1:17:30.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,担心你是不是出什么事了\N{\rENG}wondering what the hell happened to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.04,1:17:33.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我 一直都有这种感觉\N{\rENG}Okay, that is the way that I feel all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.22,1:17:35.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我把自己的生活弄得一团糟\N{\rENG}You know, like I fucked up, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.84,1:17:38.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,之前一直没管他 现在我就想去接他\N{\rENG}I left him behind and I just want to go get him.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.72,1:17:41.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,你每次送他走就会这样\N{\rENG}You always get like this when you drop him off.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.09,1:17:43.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,你很失落 然后就开始跟我吵\N{\rENG}You're sad, so you start a fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.79,1:17:48.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,他没事的 他是个很棒的孩子 好吗\N{\rENG}He's fine, he's a great kid, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.87,1:17:51.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,但事实就是他不再需要你像之前那样操心\N{\rENG}But the truth is that he does not need you the way he used to.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.79,1:17:53.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,你错过了可以陪伴\N{\rENG}You missed the opportunity to be with him
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.18,1:17:54.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,在他童年每一天的机会\N{\rENG}every day of his childhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.32,1:17:55.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,已经错过了\N{\rENG}You just did.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.14,1:17:59.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,就算你再懊恼流泪 他也已经长大了\N{\rENG}And you can cry about it, but he is growing up.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.14,1:18:02.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,其他方面你是个很好的父亲\N{\rENG}You're a great father in other ways,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.75,1:18:05.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,离婚又不是什么稀奇事\N{\rENG}you got divorced like millions of other people.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.53,1:18:06.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,要说它适合吗 当然不是\N{\rENG}Was it ideal? No.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.07,1:18:08.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是\N{\rENG}But...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.68,1:18:09.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,听着\N{\rENG}Listen,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.47,1:18:12.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果一个月后你依旧想让我辞职\N{\rENG}if in one month, you still want me to quit my job,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.74,1:18:15.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我抛弃这些年积攒下的一切跟你走\N{\rENG}and give up everything I've been working towards all these years,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.40,1:18:16.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,直说就是了\N{\rENG}just ask me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.55,1:18:19.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,但现在我这个想法是一直都有的\N{\rENG}But right now I I feel the same way I always have.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.12,1:18:21.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可以搬回美国\N{\rENG}I would move back to the US
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.29,1:18:24.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,只要你的变态前妻能共享共同监护权\N{\rENG}if that diseased ex-wife of yours give us joint custody.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.46,1:18:27.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,但每隔一周的周末就会很难熬了 杰西\N{\rENG}But every other weekend amounts to shit, Jesse.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.19,1:18:29.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,一学期差不多就有三十天\N{\rENG}That's less than 30 days a semester,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.14,1:18:32.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我们为了那样的生活来放弃现在的日子\N{\rENG}and I don't think it's worth it for us to change our entire lives
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.10,1:18:34.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,是不值得的\N{\rENG}Over that kind of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.04,1:18:35.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你说的没错  - 是吧\N{\rENG}- I know you're right.  - Right, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.29,1:18:38.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,看 我倒成了理性的那个\N{\rENG}See? I'm being the rational one.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.78,1:18:44.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是 汉克处境太糟 他是无辜的\N{\rENG}It's just... A shitty position. I mean Hank didn't do anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.47,1:18:46.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,可他却被一直忽略\N{\rENG}but he's the one getting kicked in the teeth.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.13,1:18:49.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,人或多或少都会被父母的生活所拖累\N{\rENG}We all get dragged through our parent's lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.69,1:18:52.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果不是我 你的婚姻又会是另种情况\N{\rENG}If it wasn't me, your marriage would have ended over something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.41,1:18:53.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这你很清楚  - 当然\N{\rENG}- And you know that.  - Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.89,1:18:55.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以他可能会被贫困家庭养育\N{\rENG}Or even worse he would have been raised
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.51,1:18:57.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,这更糟\N{\rENG}by two miserable parents.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.08,1:18:58.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rENG}Right...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.83,1:19:01.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真是生活一团糟啊\N{\rENG}I just really fucked that up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.65,1:19:07.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是说因为搬来巴黎和我在一起了吗\N{\rENG}You mean you fucked up by moving to Paris to be with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.40,1:19:08.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不是  - 不\N{\rENG}- No...  - No,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.69,1:19:10.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我就知道代价太大  - 我不是…\N{\rENG}- I knew that was going to cost too much.  - That's not what I meant...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.48,1:19:12.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 停 我不是这意思  - 我就知道\N{\rENG}- Stop! That's not what I meant at all.  - I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.29,1:19:14.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我劝过你的 好吗  - 别说了\N{\rENG}- I told you not to do this, okay?  - Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.16,1:19:18.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 当初我抛下一切搬去纽约\N{\rENG}Okay... I moved to New York with you for two years,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.38,1:19:20.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,跟你住了两年\N{\rENG}and gave up everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.15,1:19:22.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我需要回来生孩子\N{\rENG}But I needed to be home to give birth to the twins,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.49,1:19:23.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为双胞胎生产太复杂\N{\rENG}because it was a complicated birth,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.79,1:19:26.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还想妈妈能陪我 你也是这样想的\N{\rENG}and I wanted to be with my mother and you wanted it, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.81,1:19:27.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 对吧  - 是\N{\rENG}- Okay?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.57,1:19:29.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这是我唯一要求的事情  - 是\N{\rENG}- That's the one thing I asked from you.  - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.26,1:19:32.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,唯一一件 你就要因此永远责备我吗\N{\rENG}The one thing... and now you're gonna blame me forever?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.01,1:19:35.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,别说了 好吗\N{\rENG}Stop it, will you?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.12,1:19:36.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,别说了\N{\rENG}Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.81,1:19:40.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你不想搬回美国 我们就不搬\N{\rENG}If you don't want to move back to the States, we won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.51,1:19:41.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,就不用再说了\N{\rENG}End of story.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.30,1:19:44.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吗 我只是在想\N{\rENG}Alright? I am just trying to find a way
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.62,1:19:47.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,究竟住在哪里 我的生活才能更稳定\N{\rENG}where I can be a more consistent presence in his life
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.23,1:19:50.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,能让他生活得更好 就像一家人一样\N{\rENG}and ideally I would like to do that as a family.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.21,1:19:52.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,不然你想分居还是离婚\N{\rENG}As a family or what?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.78,1:19:55.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,这他妈是怎么说起来的\N{\rENG}What the fuck does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.72,1:19:59.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我能感受到你说的每个字\N{\rENG}I feel a passive-aggressive threat
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.78,1:20:01.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,都带有消极进攻的威胁\N{\rENG}in everything you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.06,1:20:05.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果不这样 你就会怨我一辈子的\N{\rENG}Either do this or I will resent you for the rest of our lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.02,1:20:06.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,是不是\N{\rENG}No?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.05,1:20:09.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错吧\N{\rENG}Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.31,1:20:14.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得…\N{\rENG}You know what? I'm sensing something...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.78,1:20:16.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,问题在于\N{\rENG}I, I, I think the problem is,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.52,1:20:19.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不想让我有一份稳定的工作\N{\rENG}is that you do not want me to have a more substantial job.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.54,1:20:21.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,从某种程度上来说\N{\rENG}On some level you feel threatened
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.51,1:20:23.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,你因为我的成就而有威胁感\N{\rENG}by my achieving anything
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.32,1:20:25.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,在咱俩的关系中会削减你的地位\N{\rENG}that could diminish your status in our relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.77,1:20:28.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在这段关系中的地位吗\N{\rENG}My status in our relationship?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.52,1:20:33.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我他妈在美国学校一学期教两门 好吗\N{\rENG}I teach two courses a semester at the fucking American school, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.15,1:20:35.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,真是有地位啊\N{\rENG}Wow, that's really some status!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.98,1:20:37.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 你会在我有这样一个绝佳的\N{\rENG}No, no. I don't think it's any coincidence
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.44,1:20:39.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,工作机遇之时\N{\rENG}that you feel that way at the same time
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.30,1:20:41.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,却有那样的想法绝不是偶然\N{\rENG}that I have a truly exciting job opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.62,1:20:46.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,你很清楚 这一连串的都是你在瞎想\N{\rENG}This whole train of thought is complete horseshit and you know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.58,1:20:48.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,我问你\N{\rENG}I have a question for you:
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.00,1:20:52.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果我们没有女儿 还有这些有的没的\N{\rENG}If we didn't have the girls, all our crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.40,1:20:54.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们还会在一起吗\N{\rENG}Would we even still be together?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.38,1:20:55.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.57,1:20:58.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,拜托 你他妈简直不可理喻\N{\rENG}I mean, you're the fucking mayor of the crazy town.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.20,1:20:59.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,你自己也知道啊 不是吗\N{\rENG}Do you know that? You are.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.36,1:21:01.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得 你必须搬去芝加哥\N{\rENG}You know what I think? I think you have to move to Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.92,1:21:03.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,亨利需要你\N{\rENG}I think Henry needs you,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.04,1:21:04.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我和女儿们就留在巴黎\N{\rENG}and I think I need to stay in Paris with the girls,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.81,1:21:05.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,接受这份工作\N{\rENG}and take this job.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.88,1:21:09.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,你为什么要这样 简直不可理喻\N{\rENG}Why are you doing this? That's a ridiculous idea,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.36,1:21:12.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,要我离开你和女儿们 不行\N{\rENG}Like I'm gonna lose you and the girls? No!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.04,1:21:13.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,你干嘛把所有的事情都复杂化\N{\rENG}Why do you make everything so difficult?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.76,1:21:15.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,杰西 你跟我在一起并不快乐\N{\rENG}Jesse, you're unhappy with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.39,1:21:17.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,你怪我让你离开你的儿子\N{\rENG}You're blaming me for taking you away from your son.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.73,1:21:20.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,你这样说也太莫名了\N{\rENG}That is a completely irrational response
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.27,1:21:22.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是在理清我的思路\N{\rENG}to something I'm just trying to feel my way through.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.96,1:21:25.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,听着 杰西\N{\rENG}Listen, Jesse.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.89,1:21:28.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这一个半月里\N{\rENG}We just spent the last six weeks here,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.71,1:21:31.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们过得很开心\N{\rENG}and it's been great.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.39,1:21:34.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,你每天都能思如泉涌\N{\rENG}You've been able to write every day,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.48,1:21:37.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,天气也十分美好\N{\rENG}and the weather has been nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.42,1:21:40.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 但我之前并不想来希腊  - 我知道\N{\rENG}- But I didn't want to come to Greece.  - I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.23,1:21:43.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,是吧 你无法预料下一秒会发生什么\N{\rENG}Right? There could be a revolution any second.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.65,1:21:46.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,人们会吃掉很多羊乳酪和橄榄油\N{\rENG}People eat a lot of feta and olive oil.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.58,1:21:48.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,表面上看起来很开心\N{\rENG}And they act all happy,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.33,1:21:50.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,但实际谈论的却是自己受了多少气\N{\rENG}but they actually talk about how angry they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.74,1:21:51.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就犹豫了\N{\rENG}And it confuses me,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.80,1:21:53.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不知道以后到底会怎样  - 好吧\N{\rENG}- And I don't know what's gonna happen.  - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.96,1:21:56.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,我来告诉你将来会如何\N{\rENG}Let me tell you what's gonna happen, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.09,1:21:59.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,就跟平常一样\N{\rENG}the same thing that always happens...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.17,1:22:00.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么事都没有\N{\rENG}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.80,1:22:05.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,是 你知道吗 我没有一点自由时间\N{\rENG}Right, you know what? I have had absolutely zero time for myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.07,1:22:07.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还有一万封要回复的邮件\N{\rENG}I have ten thousand emails I have to answer
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.33,1:22:08.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没处理  - 等下\N{\rENG}- That I didn't answer.  - Wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.56,1:22:09.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你以为我没有吗  - 随便了\N{\rENG}- And you think I don't?  - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.81,1:22:11.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,我整天都在做饭\N{\rENG}I spend all day making dinner,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.18,1:22:13.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,擦干你和你儿子在马桶坐垫上的尿\N{\rENG}and wiping both you and your son's pee off the toilet seat,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.68,1:22:15.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,你却在跟同行小说家侃侃而谈\N{\rENG}while you talk to your fellow novelist:
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.61,1:22:17.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,哎呀哎呀 你真是个天才\N{\rENG}Blah, blah, blah. You are a genius!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.94,1:22:21.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,哎呀哎呀哎呀哎呀 不 你才是天才\N{\rENG}Oh, blah blah blah blah. No! You are a genius!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.92,1:22:24.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们跟亨利道别那一瞬间 你却说\N{\rENG}And the second we said goodbye to Henry you suggest that
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.37,1:22:25.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还是得放弃梦寐以求的工作\N{\rENG}maybe I should give up my dream job
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.95,1:22:27.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,就因为你情绪低落吗\N{\rENG}because you feel bad?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.26,1:22:28.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是 现在它就成了你梦寐以求的了\N{\rENG}Okay, now it's your dream job.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.60,1:22:30.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,今天下午你都不确定你要接受这份工作\N{\rENG}This afternoon you weren't even sure you wanted it,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.53,1:22:31.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在就成梦寐以求的了\N{\rENG}but now it's your dream job.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.78,1:22:34.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,你说话从来就不算数是吧\N{\rENG}Do you ever listen to yourself?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.10,1:22:36.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,没错 这就是我梦寐以求的\N{\rENG}Yes, it is my dream job.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.21,1:22:38.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,我虽犹豫但不意味着我不想接受\N{\rENG}Just because I have doubts doesn't mean that I don't want it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.79,1:22:39.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,可是这跟你又有什么关系\N{\rENG}Alright, but why do you care?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.94,1:22:41.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,你每天都要在橄榄树下\N{\rENG}Every day you go on your two hours
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.43,1:22:44.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,花两个小时在冥想中散步\N{\rENG}contemplative walk under the olive trees.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.12,1:22:46.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,苏格拉底 你真该穿件袍子\N{\rENG}Socrates, oh you should get a robe.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.85,1:22:48.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,是一个小时\N{\rENG}It's an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.07,1:22:51.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 从你离开到回来\N{\rENG}No, by the time you leave and by the time you actually with us again,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.06,1:22:53.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是两个小时 换我就不行\N{\rENG}Two hours. You know, I could never do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.64,1:22:55.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,你实在太会享受了\N{\rENG}you are very good at taking care of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.38,1:22:57.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就自己照顾自己 还要操心别的事情\N{\rENG}I take care of myself and everything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.43,1:23:01.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,去哪里都是你收拾自己的 我收拾别的\N{\rENG}We go somewhere you pack your bag and I pack everything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.01,1:23:03.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,你从来都不会让我收拾女儿的东西\N{\rENG}You would never let me pack the girls' shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.55,1:23:04.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,从来都不会\N{\rENG}Never!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.23,1:23:06.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为你会忘了拿鞋子 尽带些脏内裤\N{\rENG}'Cause there would be no shoes and plenty of dirty underwear.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.78,1:23:08.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,是了是了 随便你说\N{\rENG}Yeah ok, alright, so says you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.58,1:23:09.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 你有时间思考\N{\rENG}No, I am happy that you have time
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.78,1:23:12.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,有关宇宙与生存的问题 我很开心\N{\rENG}to contemplate the universe and have existential problems...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.43,1:23:15.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为我没有 我几乎没有时间思考\N{\rENG}Because I don't. I barely have time to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.15,1:23:16.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,我上班 带孩子\N{\rENG}I work, I babysit,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.46,1:23:18.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 上班 带孩子  - 你消停会行吗\N{\rENG}- I work, I babysit.  - Could you hold on a second?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.44,1:23:20.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想上个厕所\N{\rENG}I just have to tune up the string section.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.57,1:23:22.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,知道吗\N{\rENG}You know what?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.24,1:23:24.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,在办公室我只有\N{\rENG}The only time I get to think now
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.77,1:23:26.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,拉屎的时间能思考\N{\rENG}is when I take a shit at the office.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.25,1:23:29.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,伴着屎味整理思绪\N{\rENG}I'm starting to associate the thoughts with the smell of shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.88,1:23:32.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,这句话不错\N{\rENG}That is a good line!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.15,1:23:33.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要把这话用在书里\N{\rENG}I'm going to use that in a book someday.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.71,1:23:34.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊 你一定会的\N{\rENG}Yeah, I'm sure you will.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.74,1:23:36.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,这句话就是整本书最好的句子了\N{\rENG}And that will be the best line in the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.97,1:23:41.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有 不准再把我或我说过做过的\N{\rENG}And by the way, you may never ever use me or anything I say or do
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.11,1:23:42.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,写进你那些书里了\N{\rENG}in one of your fucking books again.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.69,1:23:44.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,女儿们的也不可以\N{\rENG}and that goes for the girls, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.70,1:23:45.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,行\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.67,1:23:47.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是你不该跟作家搞在一起的 对吧\N{\rENG}You shouldn't have hooked up with a writer, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.63,1:23:50.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不会把你写进书里的\N{\rENG}You weren't in the last book or the one I'm writing now.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.33,1:23:52.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,我他妈想写什么就写什么\N{\rENG}See, I'm gonna write about whatever the fuck I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.47,1:23:55.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我们的生活还是你的素材  - 不不不\N{\rENG}- As always, our life works for you.  - No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.65,1:23:58.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,别再那装受虐媳妇的丑样子\N{\rENG}Don't give me this put-upon housewife bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.68,1:24:00.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 现在已经不是五十年代了\N{\rENG}Ok? This is not the 50s.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.13,1:24:03.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,抱歉打断你受压迫血泪史的激情讲述\N{\rENG}I'm sorry to ruin your perfect little narrative of oppression.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.27,1:24:05.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,但事实上我才是\N{\rENG}With the truth but I'm the one
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.45,1:24:07.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,那个每天在家操心琐碎的人\N{\rENG}who's at home every day dealing with the bullshit,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.87,1:24:10.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 因为你六点半才下班  - 是六点\N{\rENG}- Cause you are working till 6:30  - Six o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.03,1:24:12.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,你送女儿去学校 我去接\N{\rENG}You take the girls to school and I pick them up,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.26,1:24:14.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,这样很公平 是我们约定好的\N{\rENG}that's fair, that's our deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.21,1:24:18.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 天 我们可是住在法国巴黎  - 对\N{\rENG}- We live in Paris, France, for Christ's sakes!  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.19,1:24:21.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你每天都要提醒我这事  - 我一生\N{\rENG}- And you remind me of it every single day.  - I have orbited
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.25,1:24:24.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,都在围着你转 你知道的\N{\rENG}my entire life around you and you know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.00,1:24:27.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我很抱歉这个暑假 你的确是度假\N{\rENG}Ok? So I'm sorry if this summer's vacation, and it is a vacation,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.42,1:24:29.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为我只看到你在海里玩耍\N{\rENG}because all I've seen you do is frolic in the sea,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.59,1:24:31.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有不停地吃希腊沙拉\N{\rENG}and shove Greek salad down your throat.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.33,1:24:34.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,但这些并不能说明你花了时间\N{\rENG}Ok? But it's not indicative of you spending your life
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.13,1:24:35.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,做家务\N{\rENG}In some kind of domestic servitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.74,1:24:37.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我喜欢男人什么吗\N{\rENG}You know what I love about men?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.39,1:24:39.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们依旧相信有魔法\N{\rENG}They still believe in magic.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.38,1:24:41.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,小精灵们帮他们收拾臭袜子\N{\rENG}Little fairies around who pick up the socks,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.83,1:24:44.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,把碗洗干净\N{\rENG}little fairies unload the dishwasher,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.30,1:24:46.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,给孩子们涂防晒油\N{\rENG}little fairies sunscreen the kids,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.22,1:24:48.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,做好希腊沙拉后\N{\rENG}little fairies who make the fucking
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.03,1:24:49.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,让你吃得像头猪一样\N{\rENG}Greek salad that you eat like a pig.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.95,1:24:51.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,行了 听我说 好吗\N{\rENG}Okay, listen to me, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.62,1:24:53.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,你把我们照顾得很好\N{\rENG}You are great at taking care of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.51,1:24:54.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,这没错\N{\rENG}You are.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.88,1:24:57.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说 你念着孩子\N{\rENG}I mean... you take care of the kids,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.12,1:25:00.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,想着朋友 心系整个社会\N{\rENG}you take care of your friends, you take care of the world, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.08,1:25:02.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,在你成为一个母亲之前就已经这样了\N{\rENG}And you were like that before you were a mom,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.60,1:25:04.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在更是爱心泛滥\N{\rENG}and now its only magnified, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.55,1:25:05.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是\N{\rENG}But...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.78,1:25:07.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,这也是我这些年一直强调的\N{\rENG}and I've been telling you this for years,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.52,1:25:09.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,你得对自己上点心了 好吗\N{\rENG}now you gotta do a little bit better job
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.09,1:25:11.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,关心下自己\N{\rENG}taking care of yourself, ok? You do.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.38,1:25:13.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后不要再以关心我做借口了 好吗\N{\rENG}Okay, stop patronizing me, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.97,1:25:16.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我才是每天六点在家 不是六点半\N{\rENG}I am the one at home every day at six, not 6:30.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.91,1:25:17.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很值得信赖\N{\rENG}I am reliable.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.66,1:25:20.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,你请过保姆吗\N{\rENG}Have you ever booked a baby sitter ever in your entire life?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.09,1:25:22.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.40,1:25:24.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,女儿们的医生叫什么名字\N{\rENG}what is the name of their pediatrician?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.27,1:25:25.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要突击测试我\N{\rENG}Stop quizzing me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.27,1:25:26.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你不知道  - 好吗 你也太无聊了\N{\rENG}- You don't know.  - Alright? it's really fucking boring.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.60,1:25:29.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,是吧 行 知道吗 我每晚都在家\N{\rENG}Yeah, okay... You know what? I'm at home every night,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.51,1:25:31.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,做饭 给孩子们洗澡\N{\rENG}and I make dinner, I give bath,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.81,1:25:33.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,给她们读睡前故事\N{\rENG}and I read bedtime stories.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.00,1:25:33.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,有时候你在\N{\rENG}Sometimes you there,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.79,1:25:36.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,有时候你学校又有事\N{\rENG}sometimes you at a university event,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.24,1:25:38.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,或是巡回宣传\N{\rENG}or a publicity tour, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.45,1:25:41.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,你灵感一来就一直在写作\N{\rENG}When you get inspired you keep on writing,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.79,1:25:43.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,有时候我也会有灵感的 你知道吗\N{\rENG}I get inspired too sometimes, you know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.73,1:25:46.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,你也想写东西 很好 你写嘛\N{\rENG}You want to write? Good, write.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.40,1:25:48.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 但你记得我曾是吉他唱手\N{\rENG}No, but you remember I used to sing,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.42,1:25:50.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,还写词作曲吧\N{\rENG}and play guitar and write songs.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.58,1:25:52.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还是很喜欢做这个\N{\rENG}I'd still like to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.20,1:25:54.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我做不到 没时间\N{\rENG}But I don't get to, there isn't time.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.04,1:25:57.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,好 首先 写作并不是我的兴趣爱好\N{\rENG}Ok... well, first off: My writing isn't a hobby.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.85,1:26:00.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吗 其次 我希望你能挤出点时间\N{\rENG}Alright? Secondly, I wish you would find the time...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.73,1:26:02.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,不知道你怎么有时间\N{\rENG}you somehow manage to find the time to
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.35,1:26:04.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,抱怨一天工作八小时\N{\rENG}complain about eight hours a day!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.11,1:26:08.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,我喜欢你唱歌的样子 好吗\N{\rENG}I mean... I love the way you sing, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.89,1:26:11.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,我抛弃一切追随你\N{\rENG}I fucked up my whole life,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.34,1:26:13.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,就因为你唱歌的样子 好吗\N{\rENG}'cause the way you sing, alright?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.46,1:26:15.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你在牢骚 抱怨 忧虑中\N{\rENG}If you took one eighth of the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.90,1:26:20.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,分出八分之一的精力\N{\rENG}that you spend on bitching, whining, and worrying,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.39,1:26:23.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,放在音乐创作上\N{\rENG}if you put that energy into playing scales,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.00,1:26:25.50,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}姜戈·恩哈特{\u0}：法国著名吉他手，爵士乐史上的伟大琴师\N{\rCHS}你会成为姜戈·恩哈特这种人物的\N{\rENG}I mean you would like be fucking Django Reinhardt.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.00,1:26:31.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.63,1:26:34.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,你忘了拿鞋子\N{\rENG}You forgot your shoes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.99,1:26:57.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,你以为你赢了吗\N{\rENG}You think you're winning?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.29,1:26:59.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,很少有人能体会到\N{\rENG}Very few people realize what it's like
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.00,1:27:02.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,对事业热情洋溢的女人有了孩子的感受\N{\rENG}for an active or passionate woman to have a child.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.87,1:27:05.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,有些朋友说 看吧\N{\rENG}Some friends told me that you'll see,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.06,1:27:06.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,迟早你会想着把她们扔出窗子\N{\rENG}you'll wanna throw them out the window.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.66,1:27:09.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,但事实上我一点也不想伤害她们\N{\rENG}Okay? But the truth is that I never wanted to hurt them once,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.16,1:27:12.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我想过很多次要为自己结束这种生活\N{\rENG}but I thought about ending it all for myself a hundred times.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.60,1:27:16.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很彷徨 而你又因亨利抚养权这破事\N{\rENG}I was so confused and you were always away on a stupid book tour
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.13,1:27:17.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,总是参加售书巡回活动\N{\rENG}because of Henry's custody shit,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.91,1:27:19.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我也不想跟你徒增烦恼\N{\rENG}and I didn't want to be a burden.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.87,1:27:21.01,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}西尔维娅·普雷{\u0}：美国女诗人，于创作高峰时自杀\N{\rCHS}现在我明白为何西尔维娅·普雷\N{\rENG}Now I know why Sylvia Plath
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.01,1:27:22.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,把头放进烤面包器里\N{\rENG}put her head in a toaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.77,1:27:24.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,是烤箱\N{\rENG}It was an oven.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.20,1:27:26.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要给我咬文嚼字 你知道我的意思\N{\rENG}Don't play with words! You know what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.11,1:27:28.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,烤面包器 烤箱 都一个意思\N{\rENG}Toaster, oven! Same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.47,1:27:31.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道有多少次我独自面对女儿们的哭泣吗\N{\rENG}You know how many times I was alone with the girls crying?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.36,1:27:32.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,我完全不知道怎么办\N{\rENG}With no clue what to do? Do you know
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.94,1:27:35.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道当一个母亲不知所措时她的负罪感吗\N{\rENG}the guilt a mother feels when she doesn't know what to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.35,1:27:38.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,你以为只有你有这种感觉吗\N{\rENG}Do you think you have sole ownership of that feeling?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.88,1:27:41.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,你根本不明白好吗\N{\rENG}I don't think you understand, ok?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.69,1:27:44.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道我内心对男人恐惧的是什么吗\N{\rENG}You know what my secret fear is with every man?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.88,1:27:48.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,是他们都想把我变成一个顺从的主妇\N{\rENG}Is that they all want to turn me into a submissive housewife.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.45,1:27:52.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 没人能那样做\N{\rENG}Ok... no one could ever do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.03,1:27:54.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吗 我保证\N{\rENG}Alright? I promise it would be easier
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.90,1:27:57.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,要让你顺从什么\N{\rENG}to fit your head into a toaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.17,1:27:59.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,还不如把你的头按进烤箱里更容易\N{\rENG}than to turn you into anything submissive.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.22,1:28:02.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得我生育以后就没恢复过来\N{\rENG}I don't think I recovered since giving birth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.40,1:28:04.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,她们出生时我完全不知道怎么办\N{\rENG}When they were born I had no idea of
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.81,1:28:07.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我…人们指望女人有天生的母性\N{\rENG}what to do, I.... People expect women
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.65,1:28:11.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,好像是突然冒出来的 就像母狒狒\N{\rENG}to have this instinct that kicks in. Like a female baboon.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.30,1:28:14.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我不知道该怎么做\N{\rENG}But I had no idea how to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.61,1:28:19.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很爱她们 但我做什么都是错的\N{\rENG}I love them so much and I was doing everything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.55,1:28:21.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,你还总不在家\N{\rENG}And you were away so often,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.72,1:28:24.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,打电话问我这一天过得怎么样\N{\rENG}and calling me and asking me how my day went.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.60,1:28:25.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我都不知道怎么和你说\N{\rENG}I couldn't even say it to you
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.91,1:28:29.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得不知所措很丢人\N{\rENG}because I felt so ashamed to be so clueless.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.10,1:28:31.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我觉得你很棒  - 没有\N{\rENG}- Look, I think you did great.  - No, I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.58,1:28:34.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 你很棒 起码假装得很棒\N{\rENG}No, you did, well you did a good job faking it then.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.79,1:28:36.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,我\N{\rENG}I just ..
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.15,1:28:39.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得哄她们睡觉唯一的办法就是\N{\rENG}I remember that the only way to get them to sleep
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.01,1:28:41.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,把笨重的双人婴儿车拖下楼\N{\rENG}was to drag that stupid double
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.32,1:28:44.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,在午夜几小时几小时的散步\N{\rENG}stroller down the stairs and walk them for hours and hours
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.80,1:28:47.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,走到皮加勒再返回来\N{\rENG}in the middle of the night, all the way to Pigalle and back.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.17,1:28:49.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,我有一次差点被抢劫\N{\rENG}I almost got mugged once, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.61,1:28:51.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,那家伙放过我的唯一原因\N{\rENG}the only reason why the guy didn't attack me
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.34,1:28:53.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,是我看上去太惨了\N{\rENG}was that I looked so pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.16,1:28:55.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,过了三十五岁的唯一好处\N{\rENG}The only upside of being over 35
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.97,1:28:57.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是不用担心被强奸\N{\rENG}is that you don't get raped as much.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.48,1:29:03.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我看过这个说法 是真的  - 老天\N{\rENG}- I read it, it's true.  - Oh Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.24,1:29:07.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得我有一次\N{\rENG}Once I remember that I was watching
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.82,1:29:10.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,看到姐妹俩在跳蹦蹦床\N{\rENG}the twins on the trampoline, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.03,1:29:11.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,她们好漂亮\N{\rENG}and they looked so beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.22,1:29:15.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很开心因为她们开心\N{\rENG}and I was happy because they were happy, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.27,1:29:16.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,其中一个用呼啦圈\N{\rENG}And one of them had this...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.14,1:29:21.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,跳绳用的那个\N{\rENG}Hulla-hoop that she was using as a jump rope, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.19,1:29:22.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,另一个也想\N{\rENG}But then the other wanted it,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.39,1:29:25.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,然后她们就打起来了\N{\rENG}so they started fighting over it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.58,1:29:28.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,突然 被我看到了\N{\rENG}And all of a sudden, I saw it all, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.00,1:29:32.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有这些遗憾 嫉妒 自私\N{\rENG}All this, pity and jealousy and selfishness, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.30,1:29:39.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得我当时就在想 好吧这就是普遍人性\N{\rENG}And I remember thinking ... Ok, this is the natural human state
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.67,1:29:44.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,总是有点不满 永远不满足\N{\rENG}Always a little dissatisfied, perpetually discontented, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.81,1:29:45.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说\N{\rENG}I mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.48,1:29:47.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,看看我们\N{\rENG}Look at us.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.80,1:29:52.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们在这 在这伊甸园\N{\rENG}Here we are, we are in... you know, The Garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.11,1:29:53.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我们还在争吵\N{\rENG}And we can not stop fighting.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.32,1:29:58.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不认为人性只有一面\N{\rENG}I do not think there is one natural human state.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.07,1:29:59.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,而是多面的\N{\rENG}The human state is multiple.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.34,1:30:00.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是说 如果你看到孩子们玩耍\N{\rENG}I mean, if that's what
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.29,1:30:02.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,想到的是这个\N{\rENG}you see when you're watching the girls play
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.98,1:30:04.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,说明你很沮丧\N{\rENG}that means you're depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.35,1:30:07.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Ok...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.79,1:30:11.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 可能是吧  - 我看到她们打架时\N{\rENG}- Maybe I am.  - No. When I see them fight I see beautiful energy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.80,1:30:13.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,看到的是生命中前行的无穷力量\N{\rENG}of going forward in life and not
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.52,1:30:16.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,不让任何人踩在她们头上 夺走她们想要的\N{\rENG}letting anyone step on them or take away what they want.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.56,1:30:19.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我喜欢她们打架 这让我看到了希望\N{\rENG}You know, I like it when they fight. It gives me hope for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.55,1:30:22.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是因为你把愤怒视作一种积极情绪\N{\rENG}Well that's cause you see anger as a positive emotion, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.06,1:30:25.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,最后只会伤害你自己 你的工作 孩子和我\N{\rENG}and you only end up hurting yourself, your work, the kids, me.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.78,1:30:30.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,你从来不会生气吗\N{\rENG}And you never get angry?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.32,1:30:32.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,我生气时不会把它视作积极情绪\N{\rENG}When I do, I don't see it as a positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.40,1:30:36.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗\N{\rENG}You know something?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.50,1:30:41.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,你写的那些书 人们来找我\N{\rENG}The way you write in your books, people come up to me
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.96,1:30:45.75,ZHU,,0,0,0,,{\u1}亨利·米勒{\u0}：美国“垮掉派”作家\N{\rCHS}以为我和那些鲁莽的亨利·米勒式的男人滚床单\N{\rENG}and think that I make love to some wildcat Henry Miller type.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.03,1:30:52.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,你滚床单的方式只有一种 每次都一样\N{\rENG}You like to have sex the exact same way. Every time.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.91,1:30:56.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你说什么就是什么吧  - 亲亲 咪咪\N{\rENG}- When you got it you got it  - Kissy, kissy, titty, titty
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.62,1:30:57.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,下面\N{\rENG}Pussy...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.53,1:31:00.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是一个兴趣简单的男人\N{\rENG}I am a man of simple pleasures.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.38,1:31:03.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的 非常简单\N{\rENG}Yeah, very simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.20,1:31:06.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,我最近打算告诉你个事\N{\rENG}And I've been meaning to tell you that lately.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.93,1:31:08.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不是亨利·米勒\N{\rENG}You're no Henry Miller
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.36,1:31:10.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,在任何方面\N{\rENG}on any level.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.76,1:31:16.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗 这房间让我浑身不自在\N{\rENG}You know what? This room gives me the creeps.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.09,1:31:19.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,我本来希望有一点古典的 真正的希腊风\N{\rENG}I was expecting something quaint, like the real Greece.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.14,1:31:19.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,这地方真的很…\N{\rENG}This place is pretty real...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.71,1:31:21.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们来这到底干嘛\N{\rENG}What the hell are we doing here anyway?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.31,1:31:22.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,全部都是安排好的\N{\rENG}This is all too planned. Like,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.40,1:31:24.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们本该度过一个不错的夜晚\N{\rENG}we are supposed to have this great evening.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.62,1:31:26.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,那种自然发生的\N{\rENG}You know... there's no room for spontaneity.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.51,1:31:28.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,离我们的生活远去了\N{\rENG}It is all gone from our lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.42,1:31:30.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,对吗 这太蠢了 根本没用\N{\rENG}Right? And this is stupid and it's not working.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.39,1:31:31.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 显然是\N{\rENG}Ok... well, obviously, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.69,1:31:34.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,我诅咒阿里阿德涅和斯特凡诺斯搞这些\N{\rENG}And I curse Ariadni and I curse Stefanos for doing this.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.20,1:31:38.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧 夫妻按摩 这他妈的什么玩意儿\N{\rENG}OK. a couples' massage?! What the fuck is that!?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.10,1:31:39.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,把我都拉廉价了\N{\rENG}That sounds sleazy to me, right?
